      "I've tried to organize the solutions by the useful properties they provide. I left out map reduce and at most once as features since those aren't going to be in 2.1\r\n\r\n* Features\r\n  - Can survive client crashes: `client crash`\r\n  - Can survive server crashes: `server crash`\r\n  - Can survive connection interruptions: `conn lost`\r\n  - Can resume much later: `resume later`\r\n  - All intermediate changes seen, no squashing: `no squashing`\r\n  - extra code needed beyond query or run parameters passed: `user code`\r\n  - supports all types of queries: `all queries`\r\n* mlucy proposal\r\n   (resumable=True flag, buffers created, dropped after 1hr)\r\n  - `client crash`: no\r\n  - `server crash`: no\r\n  - `conn lost`: yes\r\n  - `resume later`: no\r\n  - `no squashing`: yes\r\n  - `user code`: yes or no depending on auto-resumption\r\n  - `all queries`: yes\r\n* timmaxw use case 1 solution\r\n  (reconnect, use return_initial to catch up)\r\n  - `client crash`: yes\r\n  - `server crash`: yes\r\n  - `conn lost`: yes\r\n  - `resume later`: yes\r\n  - `no squashing`: no\r\n  - `user code`: yes (reconnect, add return_initial, deal with dupes)\r\n  - `all queries`: yes\r\n* timmaxw use case 2 solution\r\n  (btree timestamps for resuming queries with results too large for return_initial)\r\n  - `client crash`: yes\r\n  - `server crash`: yes\r\n  - `conn lost`: yes\r\n  - `resume later`: yes\r\n  - `no squashing`: no\r\n  - `user code`: yes (need to store timestamp somewhere, dig it out for resuming)\r\n  - `all queries`: no\r\n"
